UNITED STATES of America ex rel. Thomas R. COX, Relator-Appellant v. Joseph H. WILSON, as Warden of New York State Great Meadow Prison, Comstock, New York, Respondent-Appellee. No. 376. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit June 16, 1941. Leo C, Fennelly, of New York City, for appellant Bernard L. Alderman, Asst Atty. Gen., for appellee.

Before L. HAND, SWAN, and AUGUSTUS N. HAND, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Order affirmed in open Court
